Diagnosis.
Specimens may be distinguished by: males spur short and wide, curving inward and pointed in dorsal view (Fig. 
138
), spur is located on the proximal half of the chelicerae and is equal to or less than half of the cheliceral length (Fig. 
139
), procursus tip squared off with a dorsal step (Fig. 
142
) epigynum with two prominent ridges on the MEP which are as wide as tall (Fig. 
145
), narrow PEP projection (Fig. 
144
).
